A teenage boy is in a critical condition in hospital after being stabbed during a large street brawl.

The 16-year-old, and another boy of the same age, were found with stab wounds in Tottenham, north London, in the early hours of the morning. 

Scotland Yard officers, including firearms officers, were sent to the scene in Ruskin Road at 12.30am after reports a fight was under way and that gunshots had possibly been heard.

